The available photos depend on Unsplash.com. Every ten days a new set of ten images will be made available, so you can just wait for their next update cycle to see if new photos are more to your liking.

title: i take that back.
comment: I can count the number of pictures that are available on one hand.  EDIT: i'm wrong.
You'd need two hands ;). Note that the ten available wallpapers are refreshed every ten days, so you'll get a new wallpaper every day.

title: Shame about the size limit
comment: It's a shame the photo size is limited, I only have a 4 inch screen and they look pixelated, so I'd hate to think what it's like for tablet users. 'Conserving bandwidth' is a pretty poor excuse - I don't think my data use is going to be significantly impacted by downloading one photo a day.

Unsplash did not directly link to the full-size images from their site. Recently, their site has been updated and full-size images are now downloaded automatically when on wifi. (The images can be as large as 5 MB, so this could be significant when on a limited mobile data plan.)

title: Beat me to it.

title: Great!
